messages.message: Have we changed anything with the way non-complex prompts work on build mode. Nearly all of the time now I get `(No value found)` and I need to always use complex prompts to get the results. This only seems to have happened since last week
@Prashant Kikani Seems like a related issue that you are fixing. And UAT is upgraded recently as well(?).

The issue I was fixing was "Value Error. Value not set." error. But this seems to be related to that.

I feel the root cause behind all these is the model change from OpenAI's side.
LLM is not returning answers in the desired/asked format and hence we're failing to parse the value.

I have another PR to change the OpenAI model to the March versions(i.e. `gpt-3.5-turbo-0301`) - based on which we have designed all of our prompts and parsing logic. Moving back to that, should solve most of these issues.

@Lee if you can share the document and the prompt/field name, I can test whether it's working with March version models...
